(@RangerFightingStyleArcheryId, @rangerId, @classId, @level2Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You gain a +2 bonus to attack rolls you make with ranged weapons.'),
(@RangerFightingStyleDefenseId, @rangerId, @classId, @level2Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'While you are wearing armor, you gain a +1 bonus to AC.'),
(@RangerFightingStyleDuelingId, @rangerId, @classId, @level2Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'When you are wielding a melee weapon in one hand and no other weapons, you gain a +2 bonus to damage rolls with that weapon.'),
(@RangerFightingStyleTwoWeaponFightingId, @rangerId, @classId, @level2Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'When you engage in two-weapon fighting, you can add your ability modifier to the damage of the second attack.'),
(@RangerPrimevalAwarenessId, @rangerId, @classId, @level3Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You can use your action and expend one ranger spell slot to focus your awareness on the region around you. For 1 minute per level of the spell slot you expend, you can sense whether the following types of creatures are present within 1 mile of you (or within up to 6 miles if you are in your favored terrain): aberrations, celestials, dragons, elementals, fey, fiends, and undead. This feature doesn''t reveal the creatures'' location or number.'),
(@RangerExtraAttackId, @rangerId, @classId, @level5Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You can attack twice instead of once, whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.'),
(@RangerLandsStrideId, @rangerId, @classId, @level8Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'Moving through nonmagical difficult terrain costs you no extra movement. You can also pass through nonmagical plants without being slowed by them and without taking damage from them if they have thorns, spines, or a similar hazard. In addition, you have advantage on saving throws against plants that are magically created or manipulated to impede movement, such as those created by the ''Entangle'' spell.'),
(@RangerHideInPlainSightId, @rangerId, @classId, @level10Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You can spend 1 minute creating camouflage for yourself. You must have access to fresh mud, dirt, plants, soot, and other naturally occurring materials with which to create your camouflage. Once you are camouflaged in this way, you can try to hide by pressing yourself up against a solid surface, such as a tree or wall, that is at least as tall and wide as you are. You gain a +10 bonus to Dexterity (Stealth) checks as long as you remain there without moving or taking actions. Once you move or take an action or a reaction, you must camouflage yourself again to gain this benefit.'),
(@RangerVanishId, @rangerId, @classId, @level14Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You can use the Hide action as a bonus action on your turn. Also, you can''t be tracked by nonmagical means, unless you choose to leave a trail.'),
(@RangerFeralSensesId, @rangerId, @classId, @level18Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You gain preternatural senses that help you fight creatures you can''t see. When you attack a creature you can''t see, your inability to see it doesn''t impose disadvantage on your attack rolls against it. You are also aware of the location of any invisible creature within 30 feet of you, provided that the creature isn''t hidden from you and you aren''t blinded or deafened.'),
(@RangerFoeSlayerId, @rangerId, @classId, @level20Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You become an unparalleled hunter of your enemies. Once on each of your turns, you can add your Wisdom modifier to the attack roll or the damage roll of an attack you make against one of your favored enemies. You can choose to use this feature before or after the roll, but before any effects of the roll are applied.'),
(@HunterColossusSlayerId, @hunterId, @classId, @level3Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'Your tenacity can wear down the most potent foes. When you hit a creature with a weapon attack, the creature takes an extra 1d8 damage if it''s below its hit point maximum. You can deal this extra damage only once per turn.'),
(@HunterGiantKillerId, @hunterId, @classId, @level3Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'When a Large or larger creature within 5 feet of you hits or misses you with an attack, you can use your reaction to attack that creature immediately after its attack, provided that you can see the creature.'),
(@HunterHordeBreakerId, @hunterId, @classId, @level3Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'Once on each of your turns when you make a weapon attack, you can make another attack with the same weapon against a different creature that is within 5 feet of the original target and within range of your weapon.'),
(@HunterEscapeTheHordeId, @hunterId, @classId, @level7Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'Opportunity attacks against you are made with disadvantage.'),
(@HunterMultiattackDefenseId, @hunterId, @classId, @level7Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'When a creature hits you with an attack, you gain a +4 bonus to AC against all subsequent attacks made by that creature for the rest of the turn.'),
(@HunterSteelWillId, @hunterId, @classId, @level7Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You have advantage on saving throws against being frightened.'),
(@HunterVolleyId, @hunterId, @classId, @level11Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You can use your action to make a ranged attack against any number of creatures within 10 feet of a point you can see within your weapons range. You must have ammunition for each target, as normal, and you make a separate attack roll for each target.'),
(@HunterWhirlwindAttackId, @hunterId, @classId, @level11Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You can use your action to make a melee attack against any number of creatures within 5 feet of you, with a separate attack roll for each target.'),
(@HunterEvasionId, @hunterId, @classId, @level15Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You can nimbly dodge out of the way of certain area effects, such as a red dragon''s fiery breath or a ''Lightning Bolt'' spell. When you are subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to take only half damage, you instead take no damage if you succeed on the saving throw, and only half damage if you fail.'),
(@HunterStandAgainstTheTideId, @hunterId, @classId, @level15Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'When a hostile creature misses you with a melee attack, you can use your reaction to force that creature to repeat the same attack against another creature (other than itself) of your choice.'),
(@HunterUncannyDodgeId, @hunterId, @classId, @level15Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'When an attacker that you can see hits you with an attack, you can use your reaction to halve the attack''s damage against you.'),
(@RogueExpertiseId, @rogueId, @classId, @level1Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'Choose two of your skill proficiencies, or one of your skill proficiencies and your proficiency with thieves'' tools. Your proficiency bonus is doubled for any ability check you make that uses either of the chosen proficiencies. At 6th level, you can choose two more of your proficiencies (in skills or with thieves'' tools) to gain this benefit.'),
(@RogueSneakAttackId, @rogueId, @classId, @level1Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You know how to strike subtly and exploit a foe''s distraction. Once per turn, you can deal an extra 1d6 damage to one creature you hit with an attack if you have advantage on the attack roll. The attack must use a finesse or a ranged weapon. You don''t need advantage on the attack roll if another enemy of the target is within 5 feet of it, that enemy isn''t incapacitated, and you don''t have disadvantage on the attack roll. The amount of the extra damage increases as you gain levels in this class: 2d6 at 3rd level, 3d6 at 5th level, 4d6 at 7th level, 5d6 at 9th level, 6d6 at 11th level, 7d6 at 13th level, 8d6 at 15th level, 9d6 at 17th level, and 10d6 at 19th level.'),
(@RogueThievesCantId, @rogueId, @classId, @level1Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'During your rogue training you learned thieves'' cant, a secret mix of dialect, jargon, and code that allows you to hide messages in seemingly normal conversation Only another creature that knows thieves'' cant understands such messages. It takes four times longer to convey such a message than it does to speak the same idea plainly. In addition, you understand a set of secret signs and symbols used to convey short, simple messages, such as whether an area is dangerous or the territory of a thieves'' guild, whether loot is nearby, or whether the people in an area are easy marks or will provide a safe house for thieves on the run.'),
(@RogueCunningActionId, @rogueId, @classId, @level2Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'Your quick thinking and agility allow you to move and act quickly. You can take a bonus action on each of your turns in combat. This action can be used only to take the Dash, Disengage, or Hide action.'),
(@RogueUncannyDodgeId, @rogueId, @classId, @level5Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'When an attacker that you can see hits you with an attack, you can use your reaction to halve the attack''s damage against you.'),
(@RogueEvasionId, @rogueId, @classId, @level7Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You can nimbly dodge out of the way of certain area effects, such as a red dragon''s fiery breath or an ''Ice Storm'' spell. When you are subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to take only half damage, you instead take no damage if you succeed on the saving throw, and only half damage if you fail.'),
(@RogueReliableTalentId, @rogueId, @classId, @level11Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You have refined your chosen skills until they approach perfection. Whenever you make an ability check that lets you add your proficiency bonus, you can treat a d20 roll of 9 or lower as a 10.'),
(@RogueBlindsenseId, @rogueId, @classId, @level14Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'If you are able to hear, you are aware of the location of any hidden or invisible creature within 10 feet of you.'),
(@RogueSlipperyMindId, @rogueId, @classId, @level15Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You have acquired greater mental strength. You gain proficiency in Wisdom saving throws.'),
(@RogueElusiveId, @rogueId, @classId, @level18Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You are so evasive that attackers rarely gain the upper hand against you. No attack roll has advantage against you while you aren''t incapacitated.'),
(@RogueStrokeOfLuckId, @rogueId, @classId, @level20Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You have an uncanny knack for succeeding when you need to. If your attack misses a target within range, you can turn the miss into a hit. Alternatively, if you fail an ability check, you can treat the d20 roll as a 20. Once you use this feature, you can''t use it again until you finish a short or long rest.'),
(@ThiefFastHandsId, @thiefId, @classId, @level3Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You can use the bonus action granted by your Cunning Action to make a Dexterity (Sleight of Hand) check, use your thieves'' tools to disarm a trap or open a lock, or take the Use an Object action.'),
(@ThiefSecondStoryWorkId, @thiefId, @classId, @level3Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You gain the ability to climb faster than normal; climbing no longer costs you extra movement. In addition, when you make a running jump, the distance you cover increases by a number of feet equal to your Dexterity modifier.'),
(@ThiefSupremeSneakId, @thiefId, @classId, @level9Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You have advantage on a Dexterity (Stealth) check if you move no more than half your speed on the same turn.'),
(@ThiefUseMagicDeviceId, @thiefId, @classId, @level13Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You have learned enough about the workings of magic that you can improvise the use of items even when they are not intended for you. You ignore all class, race and level requirements on the use of magic items.'),
(@ThiefThiefsReflexesId, @thiefId, @classId, @level17Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You have become adept at laying ambushes and quickly escaping danger. You can take two turns during the first round of any combat. You take your first turn at your normal initiative and your second turn at your initiative minus 10. You can''t use this feature when you are surprised.'),
(@SorcererSpellcastingFocusId, @sorcererId, @classId, @level1Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You can use an arcane focus as a spellcasting focus for your sorcerer spells.'),
(@SorcererSorceryPointsId, @sorcererId, @classId, @level2Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You have 2 sorcery points, and you gain more as you reach higher levels, as shown in the Sorcery Points column of the Sorcerer table. You can never have more sorcery points than shown on the table for your level. You regain all spent sorcery points when you finish a long rest.'),
(@SorcererFlexibleCastingId, @sorcererId, @classId, @level2Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You can use your sorcery points to gain additional spell slots, or sacrifice spell slots to gain additional sorcery points. You learn other ways to use your sorcery points as you reach higher levels.\n\n Creating Spell Slots: You can transform unexpended sorcery points into one spell slot as a bonus action on your turn. The table below shows the cost of creating a spell slot of a given level. You can create spell slots no higher in level than 5th.\n\nSpell Slot Level - Sorcery Point Cost\n1st - 2\n2nd - 3\n3rd - 5\n4th - 6\n5th - 7\n\n Converting a Spell Slot to Sorcery Points: As a bonus action on your turn, you can expend one spell slot and gain a number of sorcery points equal to the slot''s level.'),
(@SorcererMetamagicId, @sorcererId, @classId, @level3Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You gain the ability to twist your spells to suit your needs. You gain two Metamagic options of your choice. You gain another one at 10th and 17 level. You can use only one Metamagic option on a spell when you cast it, unless otherwise noted.'),
(@SorcererCarefulSpellId, @sorcererId, @classId, @level3Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'When you cast a spell that forces other creatures to make a saving throw, you can protect some of those creatures from the spell''s full force. To do so, you spend 1 sorcery point and choose a number of those creatures up to your Charisma modifier (minimum of 1 creature). A chosen creature automatically succeeds on its saving throw against the spell.'),
(@SorcererDistantSpellId, @sorcererId, @classId, @level3Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'When you cast a spell that has a range of 5 feet or greater, you can spend 1 sorcery point to double the range of the spell. When you cast a spell that has a range of touch, you can spend 1 sorcery point to make the range of the spell 30 feet.'),
(@SorcererEmpoweredSpellId, @sorcererId, @classId, @level3Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'When you roll damage for a spell, you can spend 1 sorcery point to reroll a number of the damage dice up to your Charisma modifier (minimum of one). You must use the new rolls. You can use Empowered Spell even if you have already used a different Metamagic option during the casting of the spell.'),
(@SorcererExtendedSpellId, @sorcererId, @classId, @level3Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'When you cast a spell that has a duration of 1 minute or longer, you can spend 1 sorcery point to double its duration, to a maximum duration of 24 hours.'),
(@SorcererHeightenedSpellId, @sorcererId, @classId, @level3Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'When you cast a spell that forces a creature to make a saving throw to resist its effects, you can spend 3 sorcery points to give one target of the spell disadvantage on its first saving throw made against the spell.'),
(@SorcererQuickenedSpellId, @sorcererId, @classId, @level3Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'When you cast a spell that has a casting time of 1 action, you can spend 2 sorcery points to change the casting time to 1 bonus action for the casting.'),
(@SorcererSubtleSpellId, @sorcererId, @classId, @level3Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'When you cast a spell, you can spend 1 sorcery point to cast it without any somatic or verbal components.'),
(@SorcererTwinnedSpellId, @sorcererId, @classId, @level3Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'When you cast a spell that targets only one creature and doesn''t have a range of self, you can spend a number of sorcery points equal to the spell''s level to target a second creature in range with the same spell (1 sorcery point if the spell is a cantrip).'),
(@SorcererSorcerousRestorationId, @sorcererId, @classId, @level20Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'You regain 4 expended sorcery points whenever you finish a short rest.'),
(@DraconicBloodlineDragonAncestorBlackId, @draconicBloodlineId, @classId, @level1Id, @otherRangeTypeId, 0, @feetRangeUnitId, null, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, null, 0, 0, 0, '', 'Each of the features you gain later will do Acid damage. You can speak, read, and write Draconic. Additionally, whenever you make a Charisma check when interacting with dragons, your proficiency bonus is doubled if it applies to the check.'),
